full_text:
There are also a whole slew of other, smaller factors that played into my poor GenCon experience this year, but I think many of them stem mostly from this main problem along with my chronic issues with social anxiety in general.

That's about all I have to say about that.
full_text(utf-8): b"There are also a whole slew of other, smaller factors that played into my poor GenCon experience this year, but I think many of them stem mostly from this main problem along with my chronic issues with social anxiety in general.\n\nThat's about all I have to say about that."

full_text: 3. The current most enticing prospect but also the most daunting: give up on attending GenCon for the foreseeable future and try to find some other means or activity to act as my getaway from my personal crusade to apparently work myself to death.
full_text(utf-8): b'3. The current most enticing prospect but also the most daunting: give up on attending GenCon for the foreseeable future and try to find some other means or activity to act as my getaway from my personal crusade to apparently work myself to death.'

full_text: 2. (cont) OR volunteering my time with a booth/company/organization at the con for the duration of the event. Either of these options will provide a common thread that I can follow day to day to give my experience a little more order.
full_text(utf-8): b'2. (cont) OR volunteering my time with a booth/company/organization at the con for the duration of the event. Either of these options will provide a common thread that I can follow day to day to give my experience a little more order.'

full_text: 2. I start "working" during GenCon in one form or another. This means going with express purpose of spending the whole con running Dungeon Crawl Classics or some other rpg. Multiple sessions a day for at least 2-3 of the days of the con.
full_text(utf-8): b'2. I start "working" during GenCon in one form or another. This means going with express purpose of spending the whole con running Dungeon Crawl Classics or some other rpg. Multiple sessions a day for at least 2-3 of the days of the con.'

full_text:
Basically, this all sums up to this:

1. I start actively attending GenCon with another person. This means going with someone to explicitly spend most of the con together doing scheduled events with the obvious built in time of doing individual events for our own interests.
full_text(utf-8): b'Basically, this all sums up to this:\n\n1. I start actively attending GenCon with another person. This means going with someone to explicitly spend most of the con together doing scheduled events with the obvious built in time of doing individual events for our own interests.'

full_text:
One is focused on getting to play M:tg and the other attends a lot of the very cool Writers Symposium panels. I, on the other hand, am interested in Dungeon Crawl Classics.

So it's actually us doing a lot of things individually.
full_text(utf-8): b"One is focused on getting to play M:tg and the other attends a lot of the very cool Writers Symposium panels. I, on the other hand, am interested in Dungeon Crawl Classics.\n\nSo it's actually us doing a lot of things individually."

full_text: I also attend the con every year with some of my oldest closest friends, but a serious problem finally dawned on me this year. We don't truly do much of the con together. We room together, and we go out for drinks & dinner in the evening. But, we don't con together.
full_text(utf-8): b"I also attend the con every year with some of my oldest closest friends, but a serious problem finally dawned on me this year. We don't truly do much of the con together. We room together, and we go out for drinks & dinner in the evening. But, we don't con together."

full_text: But together, those accounted for maybe 14 out of the 96 hours or so of the convention. That is far too much unscheduled time for myself. Add on top of that the fact that I had a huge issue with my mobile data (so much that it made texting & coordinating nearly impossible).
full_text(utf-8): b'But together, those accounted for maybe 14 out of the 96 hours or so of the convention. That is far too much unscheduled time for myself. Add on top of that the fact that I had a huge issue with my mobile data (so much that it made texting & coordinating nearly impossible).'

full_text: The two days I took off before GenCon was enough to have me totally prepared to take on the whole four days of the convention. The problem was, I didn't have anything to do. I had scheduled a couple of individual games to play in, I had scheduled attending my usual panels.
full_text(utf-8): b"The two days I took off before GenCon was enough to have me totally prepared to take on the whole four days of the convention. The problem was, I didn't have anything to do. I had scheduled a couple of individual games to play in, I had scheduled attending my usual panels."

full_text:
I'm happiest when I'm engaged with a task or job. I get that at work, where I'm super demanding of myself.

My vacation & relaxation time needs to have more structure to it. My introversion doesn't demand multiple continuous days of recharging.
full_text(utf-8): b"I'm happiest when I'm engaged with a task or job. I get that at work, where I'm super demanding of myself.\n\nMy vacation & relaxation time needs to have more structure to it. My introversion doesn't demand multiple continuous days of recharging."

full_text: My GenCon every year is a mish-mashed hodgepodge of completely random events. Except that I've finally realized that my vacations can't be aimless relaxation.
full_text(utf-8): b"My GenCon every year is a mish-mashed hodgepodge of completely random events. Except that I've finally realized that my vacations can't be aimless relaxation."

full_text:
I pretty much set myself up it have a bad time. On top of which, I am doing GenCon all wrong.

And I'm not saying that there is one right way for people to enjoy it. What I mean is that I am approaching it from entirely the wrong direction for me personally.
full_text(utf-8): b"I pretty much set myself up it have a bad time. On top of which, I am doing GenCon all wrong.\n\nAnd I'm not saying that there is one right way for people to enjoy it. What I mean is that I am approaching it from entirely the wrong direction for me personally."

full_text: GenCon is the only respite I give myself. My last vacation was GenCon last year. It's pretty demanding & unrealistic of me to expect this one event to be the release valve for all the pressure I put on myself all year long.
full_text(utf-8): b"GenCon is the only respite I give myself. My last vacation was GenCon last year. It's pretty demanding & unrealistic of me to expect this one event to be the release valve for all the pressure I put on myself all year long."

full_text: The truth is, my bad time was completely my own doing. Going to GenCon is THE thing I do every year. The rest of the year I bust my ass making beer because I absolutely fucking love my job, to the detriment of my own mental well being.
full_text(utf-8): b'The truth is, my bad time was completely my own doing. Going to GenCon is THE thing I do every year. The rest of the year I bust my ass making beer because I absolutely fucking love my job, to the detriment of my own mental well being.'

full_text: I got a lot of questions, from people who know how much I look forward to this convention, asking what about the con had changed to make me sour on it so quickly this year.
full_text(utf-8): b'I got a lot of questions, from people who know how much I look forward to this convention, asking what about the con had changed to make me sour on it so quickly this year.'

full_text: So, some people may have inferred that I had a really less than stellar time at GenCon this year. By Friday morning I was pretty much fed up & had drunk a six pack of beer by 5p.
